i remember implementing a basic linux shell in c according to the instructions 
of this systems programmer who used an array of function ptrs to avoid large 
switch statements and call functions based on the value of a single variable
this can be implemented for the following snippet:

// called after every move (through apply_move() !!!)
void handle_special_move(Position* pos, Move* m)
{
    printf("handling special move\n");
    switch (m->flags)
    {
        case CASTLE_FLAG:
            handle_castling(pos->bb, m, &pos->castle_rights);
            break;
        case ENPASSANT_FLAG:
            handle_enpassant(pos->player, pos->bb, pos->enpassant);
            break;
        case KNIGHT_PROMOTION:
        case BISHOP_PROMOTION:
        case ROOK_PROMOTION:
        case QUEEN_PROMOTION:
            handle_pawn_promotion(pos->bb, m); 
            break;
        case DOUBLE_PAWN_PUSH:
            pos->enpassant = m->dest + 8 * (pos->player ? 1 : -1);
            printf("handling double_pawnpush %d\n", pos->enpassant);
            break;
        default:
            pos->enpassant = INVALID_SQUARE;
            break;
    }
}

the flag is just calling one function in each case so this can be mapped onto 
function pointers turning this code into:

typedef void (*move_handler_t)(Position *pos, Move *m);

